<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1884,2019]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1884,1911]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes in Townes &amp; Townes" authorityYear="1960" box="[828,956,1885,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Acrotaphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,956,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Acrotaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: 1) margin of gena behind eyes convex in dorsal view; 2) posterior ocelli separated from eyes by 0.6× its diameter in dorsal view; 3) mesosoma orange with pronotum black, except its distal half orange and metapleuron black; 4) metasoma orange with tergites V+ black; 5) ovipositor slender, 1.5× as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
